headlines.description: Jalen Brunson had 22 of his career-high 31 points in No. 1 Villanova's dominating first half and Omari Spellman scored 27 to help lead the Wildcats to an 87-67 rout of Temple on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson leads No. 1 Villanova in rout of Temple

headlines.description: Tyler Davis recorded a double-double before halftime and No. 9 Texas A&M put seven players in double figures while rolling over Savannah State 113-66 on Wednesday night.

headlines.description: Keenan Evans scored 16 points and No. 24 Texas Tech defeated Kennesaw State 82-53 on Wednesday night for its first win as a ranked team in eight years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Evans leads No. 24 Texas Tech over Kennesaw State 82-53

headlines.description: Matt Harris scored 27 points and reached 1,000 career points, and UMass Lowell beat Boston University 87-82 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris reaches 1,000 career points, UMass Lowell tops BU

headlines.description: Francis Alonso scored 19 points with five 3-pointers, Marvin Smith added 15 points with three 3s, and UNC Greensboro rallied to for its third-straight win, 71-58 over UNC Wilmington on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UNC Greensboro rallies to beat UNC Wilmington 71-58

headlines.description: Tarin Smith came off the bench to score 16 points and Eric Williams Jr. added 10 points, grabbed 13 rebounds and dished five assists as Duquesne won its fourth straight game, beating winless Mississippi Valley State 73-49 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith, Williams power Duquesne past winless MVSU, 73-49

headlines.description: Ivan Gandia-Rosa scored 16 of his 24 points in the final 6:45 to help North Florida beat Florida International 87-85 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gandia-Rosa leads late surge; North Florida beats FIU 87-85

headlines.description: Amanze Egekeze hit six 3-pointers and scored a career-high 32 points, 19 in the second half, and Belmont pulled away for an 82-63 win over Milwaukee on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Egekeze scores 32, Belmont pulls away from Milwaukee 82-63

headlines.description: Aaron Jordan scored 22 points, Trent Frazier added 20, and Illinois beat Longwood 92-45 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illinois routs Longwood 92-45 behind Jordan, Frazier

headlines.description: Markel Crawford scored 16 points to lead four in double figures as Mississippi beat Sam Houston State 82-69 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ole Miss with balanced attack, beats Sam Houston St. 82-69

headlines.description: Jimmy Whitt scored 19 points and dished eight assists, leading five players into double-figure scoring as Southern Methodist continued its home court dominance, turning away New Orleans, 79-66 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: SMU's home streak reaches 29 games, tops New Orleans 79-66

headlines.description: Zach Jackson scored 22 points, JT Gibson added a career-high 17, and Omaha held off Arkansas State to win its second game of the season, 77-74 on Wednesday night and snap a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Omaha beats Arkansas State 77-74

headlines.description: Kavion Pippen and Armon Fletcher each pumped in 24 points as Southern Illinois snapped a two-game losing streak and kept Jackson State winless on the road with 69-51 decision Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pippen, Fletcher lead S. Illinois past Jackson St., 69-51

headlines.description: Donte Thomas scored 12 points to lead five in double figures as Bradley shot 61 percent from the floor to rout Little Rock 86-46 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bradley shots 61 percent from field, beats Little Rock 86-66

headlines.description: Cortez Edwards scored 13 of his 22 points in the first half and Southern Miss got off to a big start and defeated Alabama A&M 69-54 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards scores 22, Southern Miss whips Alabama A&M 69-54

headlines.description: Aaron Epps scored a career-high 26 points and Tremont Waters blocked a game-tying 3-point attempt in the final seconds as LSU defeated Houston 80-77 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Epps leads LSU past Houston 80-77

headlines.description: Andre Spight had seven 3-pointers and 27 points, Anthony Johnson scored 23 points with five 3s and Northern Colorado rolled to an 83-63 win over Denver on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spight has 7 3s, 27 points, N Colorado whips Denver 83-63

headlines.description: Chandler Hutchison had 27 points and 11 rebounds, Christian Sengfelder scored six of his 12 points in double-overtime and Boise State beat Grand Canyon 85-80 on Wednesday night for its sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hutchison leads Boise State over Grand Canyon, 85-80 in 2OT

headlines.description: Elijah Brown scored 22 points, and Payton Pritchard and Kenny Wooten had 18 each to help Oregon fend off Portland State 95-84 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown's 22 helps Oregon hold off Portland State 95-84

headlines.description: Jordan Hill scored 21 points and Josh Hearlihy added another 20 and Seattle needed a late rally to get past in-state, Division II rival St. Martin's, 88-72 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hill, Hearlihy lead Seattle past D-II St. Martin's, 88-72

headlines.description: Terrell Carter II scored 19 points to lead five in double figures as Fresno State shot 55 percent from the floor to rout winless Arkansas-Pine Bluff 78-52 on Wednesday night for its seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fresno State routs Arkansas-Pine Bluff 78-52

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
